                           below);&#xD; elements of the punctuation signs and of the crux
                           ansata.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">The handwriting seems to have be
                        executed by a trained, but very uncertain hand. It is characterized by
                        slightly right-sloping letters, rounded and curved letter shapes (e.g., ሰ በ
                        ወ). A few letters appear more angular (e.g., መ ዐ).
                        <!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h3" script="Ethiopic"> Some distinctive
                        features:<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h4" script="Ethiopic"> - ጵ has the 6th order marker set up on
                        the vertical stroke at the top, oriented to the left (e.g., <locus target="#26va">26va</locus> l.23, 83rb
                        l.11);<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h5" script="Ethiopic"> - ሎ has the 7th order marker at the
                        top, not in the middle (e.g., <locus target="#102ra">102ra</locus> l.3); a
                        few times it appears attached directly at the body of the letter, without
                        horizontal stroke (<locus target="#103vb">103vb</locus>);<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h6" script="Ethiopic"> - the tops of መ ሠ ወ are slanted to the
                        left;
                        <!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h7" script="Ethiopic"> - መ and ሙ have the right loop detached
                        from the ruled line;
                        <!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h8" script="Ethiopic"> - ፲ appears occasionally in the form
                        with a ring (<locus target="#42vb">42vb</locus>
                        l.10);<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h9" script="Ethiopic"> - ፬ tends to triangular shape,
                        downwards
                        oriented;<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h10" script="Ethiopic"> - ፮ is with the loop open, looking
                        like “compressed” ፯ (e.g., <locus target="#114rb">114rb</locus>).<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                  </handDesc>
